            ],
            "weighting": "<dd>20%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 28/08/2026 5:00 pm</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L01, L02, L04",
            "mode": "Written",
            "category": "Computer Code, Paper/ Report/ Annotation",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>Students must apply predictive modelling methods to a dataset and recommend the best solution for a business problem. More specifically, they should prepare and clean dataset provided, build and tune linear regression, logistic regression, and tree-based models, and incorporate time series analysis where the data has a temporal structure. Students then compare model performance and justify their final recommendation. This is important because it gives students hands-on practice with the fundamentals of predictive modelling, building a foundation for next assignments.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Submit through Blackboard.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>A <a href=\"https://policies.uq.edu.au/document/view-current.php?id=184\">penalty</a> of 10% of the maximum possible mark will be deducted per 24 hours from time submission is due for up to 7 days. After 7 days, you will receive a mark of 0.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>"
        },
        {
            "assessment_detail_section_id": "assessment-detail-1",
            "assessment_title": "Machine Learning Skills Quiz (A2)",
            "special_indicators": [
                {
                    "special_indicators_class": "icon--education--bookmarks-document icon-text--small",
                    "special_indicator_text": "Identity Verified"
                },
                {
                    "special_indicators_class": "icon--how-youll-learn--multiple-circle-1 icon-text--small",
                    "special_indicator_text": "In-person"
                }
            ],
            "weighting": "<dd>30%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> Week 9</p>\n<p>\n</p><p>In-Person during your seminar.</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L01, L02, L04",
            "mode": "Written",
            "category": "Examination",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>Students must complete an in-person quiz covering the concepts taught across the first half of the course. For example, answering questions on data preparation, linear and logistic regression, time series analysis, tree-based methods, support vector machines, clustering, ensemble methods, and unsupervised machine learning. It includes selecting and justifying the right method for a given business scenario. This is important because it independently verifies each student's own understanding under exam conditions.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>This is an in-person quiz. Students must complete it during class time.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/deferring-exam#3\">defer this exam</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>This is a timed quiz that must be completed in person during the scheduled class session.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/deferring-exam#3\">defer this exam</a>.</p>"
        },
        {
            "assessment_detail_section_id": "assessment-detail-2",
            "assessment_title": "Advanced Machine Learning Project (A3)",
            "special_indicators": [],
            "weighting": "<dd>50%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 30/10/2026 5:00 pm</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L03, L04, L05",
            "mode": "Written",
            "category": "Computer Code, Project",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>Students must design and implement a dual model that combines unsupervised and supervised machine learning into one single pipeline. For example, using clustering or dimensionality reduction to segment customers or engineer novel features, then feeding that output into a supervised model that predicts a business outcome, before evaluating alternatives and presenting a clear, justified business recommendation. This is important because machine learning systems chain these stages rather than using them in isolation, so the task asks students to combine techniques from across the course into a single solution to a business problem.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Submit through Blackboard.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>A <a href=\"https://policies.uq.edu.au/document/view-current.php?id=184\">penalty</a> of 10% of the maximum possible mark will be deducted per 24 hours from time submission is due for up to 7 days. After 7 days, you will receive a mark of 0.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>"
        }
